International Dimensions of Business Final Project¶

The dataset we are analyzing is coming from a Kaggle posting where they got their information from VGCharts as the post acknowledged. VGChartz is a video game industry research firm that hosts a game database system that features current and legacy video game sales data among providing other content such as news, sales (discounts), reviews, articles, and a social network supported with a community forum.

About the Dataset¶

This dataset contains a list of video games with sales greater than 100,000 copies. It was generated by a scrape of vgchartz.com.

Fields include

  • Rank - Ranking of overall sales

  • Name - The games name

  • Platform - Platform of the games release (i.e. PC,PS4, etc.)

  • Year - Year of the game's release

  • Genre - Genre of the game

  • Publisher - Publisher of the game

  • NA_Sales - Sales in North America (in millions)

  • EU_Sales - Sales in Europe (in millions)

  • JP_Sales - Sales in Japan (in millions)

  • Other_Sales - Sales in the rest of the world (in millions)

  • Global_Sales - Total worldwide sales.

The script to scrape the data is available here. It is based on BeautifulSoup using Python. There are 16,598 records. 2 records were dropped due to incomplete information.

In [37]:
fig, axs = plt.subplots(figsize=(20, 10))


axs.bar(platform_sales_jap['Platform'], platform_sales_jap['JP_Sales'])
axs.bar(platform_sales_NA['Platform'], platform_sales_NA['NA_Sales'])
axs.bar(platform_sales_EU['Platform'], platform_sales_EU['EU_Sales'])
axs.bar(platform_sales_Other['Platform'], platform_sales_Other['Other_Sales'])

axs_combined = fig.add_subplot()


axs_combined.bar(platform_sales_jap['Platform'], platform_sales_jap['JP_Sales'], align='center', label='platform Jap',alpha=1)
axs_combined.bar(platform_sales_NA['Platform'], platform_sales_NA['NA_Sales'], align='center', label='platform NA',alpha=0.5)
axs_combined.bar(platform_sales_EU['Platform'], platform_sales_EU['EU_Sales'], align='center', label='platform EU',alpha=0.5)
axs_combined.bar(platform_sales_Other['Platform'], platform_sales_Other['Other_Sales'], align='center', label='platform Other',alpha=0.5)

axs_combined.set_xlabel('platform')
axs_combined.set_ylabel('Sales')


axs_combined.set_title('Combined Sales by platform')
axs_combined.legend()


plt.show()

#this combines all of the past graphs and stacks them so you can see the differences between the regions
